Wash and dry all produce. Pat @chicken breasts{12%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}. Season all over with plenty of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a large drizzle @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned on surface and no longer pink in center, ~{5-7%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #plate{} and set aside.

Meanwhile, place @water{2/3%cup} and @chicken stock concentrate{1} in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave on high until very hot, about ~{2%minutes}. Carefully remove bowl from microwave and stir in @couscous{1/2%cup}, @butter{1%tablespoon}, and a large pinch of @salt{}. Cover with #plastic wrap{} and set aside.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed). Core and dice @roma tomato{1}(cored and diced). In a #small bowl{}, mix @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} (to taste), and a pinch of @salt{}. Stir in water, 1 tsp at a time, until you reach a loose, drizzly consistency.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Stir in @peas{4%ounce}, tomato, half the scallions, half the @almonds{1%ounce}, half the @Turkish spice blend{1%tablespoon} (use the rest as you like), and a large pinch of @salt{}. Cook, stirring, until fragrant and peas are warmed through, about ~{1%minute}.

Remove plastic wrap from bowl with couscous. Fluff couscous with a #fork{}. Stir in veggies from pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide couscous and chicken between plates. Drizzle with crema. Garnish with remaining scallions and almonds. Cut @lemon{1} into quarters and serve on the side for squeezing over.

> TIP: Slice chicken first for easier eating.